CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 17, 1973, pg. 12 reads: "Female Football Savvy! - Pretty Carla Jean Arter, a member of the smart set participating in Female Football Clinic held each Tuesday evening in the Pittsburgh Room, Hotel William Penn, gets first hand information on protective measures practiced by players. Dwight White, above, and L.C. Greenwood, seated, two the the Pittsburgh Steelers stars who volunteer their time as instructors.  "Nice work," the "pros" say. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dwight White, supporting Carla Jean Arter while having her ankle wrapped by L.C. Greenwood, in William Penn Hotel during a Female Football Clinic, another version
